  "text": "The mechanism of ruptured HCC is poorly understood. The postulated mechanisms include rapid growth of tumor and necrosis, rupture by splitting of the overlying normal hepatic parenchyma or erosion of a vessel and occlusion of the hepatic veins by a tumor thrombus [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
